# Design System Enforcement

This rule enforces strict adherence to the CentaurOS design system tokens and prevents the introduction of hardcoded values.

## 1. Color Tokens (Strict)

**NEVER** use hardcoded color classes. You must use the semantic tokens.

### Text Colors
| ❌ Forbidden | ✅ Required Token | Description |
|--------------|-------------------|-------------|
| `text-slate-900` | `text-foreground` | Primary text |
| `text-slate-600/500/400` | `text-muted-foreground` | Secondary/muted text |
| `text-white` | `text-primary-foreground` | Text on primary background |
| `text-red-600/500` | `text-destructive` | Error text |
| `text-green-600/500` | `text-status-success` | Success text |
| `text-amber-600/500` | `text-status-warning` | Warning text |
| `text-blue-600/500` | `text-status-info` | Info text |
| `text-cyan-*` | `text-international-orange` | Active state / Brand accent |

### Background Colors
| ❌ Forbidden | ✅ Required Token | Description |
|--------------|-------------------|-------------|
| `bg-white` | `bg-background` or `bg-card` | Page/Card background |
| `bg-slate-50/100` | `bg-muted` or `bg-secondary` | Muted background |
| `bg-red-50/100` | `bg-status-error-light` | Error background |
| `bg-green-50/100` | `bg-status-success-light` | Success background |
| `bg-amber-50/100` | `bg-status-warning-light` | Warning background |
| `bg-blue-50/100` | `bg-status-info-light` | Info background |
| `bg-cyan-*` | `bg-international-orange` | Active state / Brand accent |

### Border Colors
| ❌ Forbidden | ✅ Required Token | Description |
|--------------|-------------------|-------------|
| `border-slate-200/300` | `border` | Default border |
| `border-red-200/300` | `border-destructive` | Error border |
| `border-input` | `border-input` | Input border |

## 2. Component Usage

**NEVER** build custom components when a UI primitive exists.

### Cards
❌ **Forbidden:**
```tsx
<div className="rounded-lg border bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
  ...
</div>
```

✅ **Required:**
```tsx
<Card>
  <CardHeader>...</CardHeader>
  <CardContent>...</CardContent>
</Card>
```

### Badges
❌ **Forbidden:**
```tsx
<span className="rounded-full bg-red-100 text-red-800 px-2 py-1">
  Error
</span>
```

✅ **Required:**
```tsx
<StatusBadge status="error">Error</StatusBadge>
```

## 3. Navigation Active States

**NEVER** use Cyan/Blue for active states. CentaurOS uses **International Orange**.

❌ **Forbidden:**
```tsx
className={cn(isActive ? "bg-cyan-50 text-cyan-600" : "...")}
```

✅ **Required:**
```tsx
className={cn(isActive ? "bg-orange-50 text-international-orange" : "...")}
```

## 4. Spacing

Use the spacing constants from `@/lib/design-system` where possible, or standard Tailwind spacing classes (`space-y-6`, `gap-4`).

## 5. Enforcement Checklist

Before submitting code:
- [ ] Grep for `text-slate-` and `bg-slate-` -> 0 matches expected
- [ ] Grep for `bg-white` -> 0 matches expected
- [ ] Grep for `text-red-` -> 0 matches expected (use `destructive`)
- [ ] Grep for `bg-cyan-` -> 0 matches expected
- [ ] Verify `Card` component is used for all containers
- [ ] Verify `StatusBadge` is used for all status indicators
